cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.LG

This paper focuses on the energy-aware design of network selection, subchannel, and power allocation in cellular and Wi-Fi networks, while taking into account the traffic delay of mobile users. This involves optimization techniques and predictive information to improve power-delay tradeoff. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely categories include cs.IT (Information Theory) for the optimization techniques, cs.SY (Systems and Control) for the control aspect, cs.MM (Multimedia) for the consideration of traffic demands, and cs.LG (Machine Learning) for the use of predictive information.
